3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses mathematical tesselations to model biological tissues, which is a topic within discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper uses persistent homology to extract topological information from images, which is a technique commonly used in computational geometry. 
5. q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods) - The paper deals with analyzing biological tissues using quantitative methods, which could be relevant to this sub-category.
